				<h5>The Project</h5>
				<p>Opiniony is the result of a three term capstone software engineering project in computer science, at Western Oregon University, in Monmouth. Oregon. 
					Have you ever needed to hold a vote in a group of friends or colleagues and wanted to avoid the effects of peer pressure swaying the vote? 
					Our app can help users with this need by allowing them to quickly create a poll with anonymous voting so user’s opinions can be kept private. 
					The app includes many different types of polls including yes/no, multiple choice, and multi-round multiple choice polls, allowing the creation of 
					a poll that best fits a user’s needs. The Opiniony Voting App features flexible polling time, allowing the creator to set the closing of a poll for
					any future date and time; and it allows the option of having the poll open at a future date and time, giving voters a chance to research and consider
					their options before casting their vote.  The Opiniony Voting App also allows the user to make the poll private to specific users. Finally, our app features
					text-to-speech functionality, allowing users to have the poll title, description and options read aloud.</p>
